           The Newcastle Handirom - an aid for the handicapped
 
 
 
 
Introduction:
 
 The Handirom was developed to enable a person with limited motor control
to operate a microcomputer.  The  control  over  the  computer,  although
limited,  will  present  the  user  with full control over wordprocessing
utilities such as View 3.0 and  Wordwise  Plus,  various spreadsheets and
databases  or  even to write and run their own  programs  in  a  language
environment such as Basic, Comal, Pascal or Lisp etc.
 
 In operation, the system claims the lower part of the screen on which it
draws up a grid representing  the  keys  on  the computer keyboard (in an
optimised  order).  The  grid  is scanned vertically whenever the program
requires keyboard input. Operation of  a  button  connected to the "fire"
button inputs on the Analogue socket at the  rear  of  the  computer will
cause  the  grid  to  be scanned horizontally until either the button has
been pressed again to select  a  letter  or command, or the grid has been
scanned horizontally twice. In this case the line is assumed to have been
wrongly selected and the vertical scan resumes.
 
 A useful feature of the  Handirom  is  that  the  keyboard  operation is
mostly unaffected and the two input devices may be used together.
 
 Five grid layouts are available; lower case, upper case, common words, a
control screen with function key  emulator and a "*" command screen. Each
of the grids also contains a  number  of commands which will be described
later.
 
 The microcomputer system must be  fitted  with a bank of sideways ram in
order for the Handirom to work. In this way, the whole of the user memory
is available for documents or programs.
 
 In  addition to the grids  mentioned  above,  custom  wordlists  may  be
created as  described  under  the section "Editing wordlists" on page 9.
These wordlists (of which three are supplied on the disc) are loaded into
sideways ram also, again maximising the amount of user ram.
 
Note:
 As a number of sideways  ram  modules  are commercially available, it is
unlikely that the Handirom has been tested with all of them. In the event
of the Handirom not working please write to  the address given at the end
of this guide giving full system details and the  type  of  sideways  ram
fitted.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
