Handirom initialisation:
 
Having verified that sideways ram  is  available  and  with  some form of
switch  connected  to  the  analogue  port,  you  are ready to  load  the
Handirom.
 
 Insert the disc into the  default disc drive and, while holding down the
SHIFT key, depress the BREAK key momentarily. If all is well, you will be
greeted  by  the  Handirom  welcome  screen.  Operating   the  switch  or
depressing any key (with the exception of the escape and break keys) will
prompt you for the sideways ram bank  that  you  wish  to  use  (refer to
manufacturers data).
 
 If you do not wish to use socket 7 (Master) or socket 15 (BBC) (assuming
that they are available) then  selecting  the  NO  option  will  list the
sideways  firmware  installed  and  prompt  for bank 4-7 (Master) or 8-15
(BBC).
 
 Upon selection of a suitable  socket,  the  Handirom  is loaded from the
disc and the user is asked to select the  speed  of the scan. Don't worry
if the speed is not quite right, as it can be adjusted later.
 
 The sound on/off option is  next.  This just "blips" on each step of the
horizontal or vertical scan. Again, this option can be adjusted later.
 
 Now select the wordprocessor option.  This  simply means that the system
will automatically insert spaces after a word  has been selected from the
wordlist or common words grid or even after  a  full  stop  (useful  when
writing  a  letter).  In  addition,  the full stop will cause the capital
letters screen to be selected for  one  character  only, after which, the
lower case screen will be selected.
 
 The wordlist required may now  be  loaded.  Three  examples:  W.STDWORD,
W.TEST  and W.NEWWORD are supplied on the disc. The program "EDIT",  also
on the  disc  will allow the editing or creation of custom wordlists with
the Handirom active.  About 9K of a 16K bank of sideways ram is available
for the wordlist selected.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
