Saving the configuration:
 
  If you are unfamiliar with  the  Handirom  please  answer  no  to  this
option.
 
  A  yes  answer to save  the  configuration  will  prompt  for  a  blank
formatted disc to  be  placed  into the current drive.  Pressing a key or
the  switch  will  save the whole  of  the  sideways  ram  (Handirom  and
wordlist) together with details of  socket number and options selected to
the disc.  By copying the program  "SRLOAD"  onto  the disc (BBC B only),
the system may be loaded in with just SHIFT-BREAK,   without  the need to
step through the welcome and option screens again.
 
  This method has the added advantage that it allows easy distribution of
the program throughout a class,   enabling each pupil to have his/her own
copy without the expense of multiple master copies (no,  we don't mind!).
 
  The command below will work with most disc filing systems:
 
          *COPY <source> <destination> <filename>
 
  e.g. Assuming a single disc drive as drive number 0,  type:
 
          *COPY 0 0 SRLOAD
 
  followed by return.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
