 These commands will now be described:
 
Command: *BEEP / *NOBEEP
Description: Turns grid blip on or off.
 
Command: *BOOT (<drv>)
Description: Execute !BOOT file on disc.
 
Command: *CATALL
Description: Catalogue all files on ADFS disc.
 
Command: *CLOSE
Description: Close any open files. Equivalent to CLOSE#0 in BASIC.
 
Command: *EXPLAIN
Description: Catalogues disc and if any BASIC programs are found that
have a REM statement in the first line, EXPLAIN will echo the associated
text to the screen. Very useful for finding programs, latest versions etc.
 
Command: *EXPALL
Description: Performs the EXPLAIN command in all directories from the
currently selected one on an ADFS disc.
 
Command: *FILESYS
Description: Returns currently selected filing system.
 
 
 
 
                                  Page 7
 
 
           The Newcastle Handirom - an aid for the handicapped
 
 
 
 
 
Command: *ON / *OFF
Description: Turns Handirom  on or off.
 
Command: *ROMS (<rom>)
Description: Sideways firmware lister.
 
Command: *SPEED <0 - 9>
Description: Selects scanning speed for Handirom.
 
Command: *WLOAD <fsp>
Description: Loads a custom wordlist into Handirom.
 
Command: *WPON / *WPOFF
Description: Turns wordprocessor mode on or off.
 
Commands may be entered in upper or lower case and may be prefixed by the
letter "H" if necessary (e.g. *HON etc)
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
